(139, NULL, 'Arizona Vocational Training Centre', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'info@arizonavtc.co.tz', 742466965, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'MIKOCHENI A, Opposite TANESCO, Mwai Kibaki Rd, Dar es Salaam', 'www.arizonavtc.co.tz', '-', '', '<p style=\"margin-block: 0px 0.9rem; color: rgb(122, 122, 122); font-family: Outfit, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bolder;\">Arizona Vocational Training Centre</span>&nbsp;(REG/NACTVET/1056) is a premier institution dedicated to providing high-quality vocational and technical education in Tanzania.</p><p style=\"margin-block: 0px 0.9rem; color: rgb(122, 122, 122); font-family: Outfit, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify;\">Our aim is to empower individuals with the skills and knowledge they need to excel in various industries and contribute to the socio-economic development of the country.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 12:18:36', '2024-07-28 12:18:36'),
(140, NULL, 'Tegeta Vocational Training Centre (TVTC)', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'vetadsmzone@veta.go.tz', 713323001, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Dar es Salaam', 'https://veta.go.tz › vetcat › listCourse ·', '-', '', 'Tegeta Vocational Training Centre in Tanzania is a VETA Registered Centre with a vision to empower and prepare their students for the labour market and self-employment (chuo cha Tegeta Vocational Training Centre | VETA Tegeta Vocational Training Centre). Their mission is to create a good learning environment which meets the Education, Training and Development expectations of their students.\r\nA student wishing to study at Tegeta Vocational Training Centre should apply online or physically attend to Tegeta Vocational Training Centre to seek for admissions or fetch the application form.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 12:24:17', '2024-07-28 12:24:17'),
(141, NULL, 'VETA Kipawa- ICT CENTER', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'kict@veta.go.tz', 222843361, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Karakata, Kipawa Dar es Salaam TZ, 40040', 'https://vetakipawa.ac.tz', '-', '', 'I am delighted that you have decided to visit our website. I am sure you will enjoy browsing through it and learning something you didn’t know about before.\r\nVETA Kipawa Information Communication Technology Center is a newly established Institute by our Government through a soft loan from The Government of South Korea. \r\nCOURSE COMPETENCES • Connect and use computer and its peripherals. • Create and prepare documents. • Formulate and analyze data. • Create and Design Publications. • Prepare presentation. • Working with internet, send and receive emails. COURSE CONTENT • Introduction to Computer and its peripherals • Document preparation and formation. (Microsoft Office Word) • Data preparation, formation and analysis (Microsoft Office Excel) •', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 12:29:45', '2024-07-28 12:29:45'),
(142, NULL, 'Kaluta Vocational Training Centre', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'info@kalutavtc.ac.tz', 222172282, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Mtaa wa Longido, Dar es Salaam', 'https://kalutavtc.ac.tz', '-', '', 'University college provides courses  for (VETA)curriculum  studies, and is under NACTE registration. The college is situated at Magomeni Mikumi Kinondoni District,Dar es Salaam Region.\r\nCollege have extensively and experienced training staffs can able to teach different subjects of field technician by practice.   \r\nThe College also provide   better services of boarding accommodation for the students for the whole day, in according to education sector. It also provides trainings for VETA curriculum through courses as follows;\r\nElelctrical Homes,cars,electronics, Satelite dish,welding,electrical fence,automatic gates,parking shades and so forth..', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 12:59:28', '2024-07-28 12:59:28'),
(143, NULL, 'ABC Vocational Training College', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'abcvtc1992@gmail.com', 754693725, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Arusha', 'https://abcvtc1992.blogspot.com', '-', '', 'Arusha Technical College (ATC) is improving access and quality of vocational education and training in Tanzania by opening chapter highlights the situation of young people and their participation in the labour market. ATC through VET department has motivated students, career counselling, honour VET education, competent instructors and adequacy of infrastructure resources throughout the years while improving internet connectivity to facilitate modern learning and 21st century skills.\r\nThe Department of Vocational Education and Training Offers part-time courses in Engineering, Science and Technology. It is also responsible for VET Programs whereby Primary school leavers as well as secondary school leavers have an opportunity to be trained as artisan under Vocational Education and Training Authority (VETA) mandate within a duration ranging from one to three years. Once completed VET programs and awarded National Vocational Award NVA) level III, it is possible for the successful student to progress further toTechnical Education Training (TET) programs through a special programme known as Pre-Technology Programme offered at Arusha Technical College for about three months to persue the National Vocational Award.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 13:13:37', '2024-07-28 13:13:37'),
(144, NULL, 'Arusha Vocational Training Centre', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'arushavtc@veta.go.tz', 736500507, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'ARUSHA VTC  P.O.Box 509 ARUSHA', 'https://veta.go.tz › vetcat › centre ›', '-', '', 'Thank	you	very	much	for	your	valuable	visit	to	Tanzania	particularly Arusha	Vocational	Education	and	\r\nTraining	Centre.	We	felt	very	proud	to	be	visited	by	the	Virgin	Media	group.\r\nTeaching	 and	 learning	 is	 one	 of the	 most	 delightful	 activities	 in	 life	 when	 it	 is	 carried	 out	 in	\r\naccordance	 with	 a	 well	 structured	 education	 system.	 Vocational	 Education	 and	 Training	 Authority	\r\n(VETA)	 is	 one	 of	 an	 Autonomous	 Government	 agency	 	 which	 imparts	 skills	 and	 knowledge	 to	 its	\r\ntrainees that	they	may	either	get	Formal	or	Informal	Employment.\r\nI	wish	to	express	my	deepest	gratitude	to	Meserani	Project coordinator Mr.	Peter	and	his	wife	Diane	\r\nfor	 connected	 	 Arusha	 Vocational	 Training	 Centre with	 the	 Virgin	 Media group	 from	 England.	\r\nHowever	 special	 thanks	 should	 go	 to Virgin	 Media	 group	 Leaders	 for	 their	 moral	 and	 material	\r\nsupport to	 our	 Centers. You	 sincerely provided	 us valuable	 items	 and	 tools, 13 laptops, two\r\nprojectors,	speakers,	wireless mouse and	Electrical	tools.\r\nWe	are	proud	of	having	8	trainees	from	Meserani	project,	they	are	very	friendly	and	capable	of	their	\r\nfield.\r\nI take	this	opportunity	to	humbly	welcome you again	believing that our	connection	will	be	useful to all	of	us.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 13:20:34', '2024-07-28 13:20:34'),
(145, NULL, 'VETA Arusha HQ', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'arushavtc@veta.go.tz', 622294243, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Arusha', 'https://veta.go.tz › vetcat › centre', '-', '', 'The Vocational Education and Training Authority (VETA) is a government institution mandated the role of providing, promoting, and facilitating financial support for providing of Vocational Education and Training system in Tanzania.\r\nVETA training programmes are organized in thirteen occupational sectors namely, Mechanical; Electrical; Civil and Building Engineering; Automotive; Commercial Services and Business Support; Clothing and Textile; Transport; Mining; Printing; Cosmetology; Agriculture and Food Processing; and Hospitality, Tourism and Travel Agency and Fine and Performing Arts.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 13:28:55', '2024-07-28 13:28:55'),
(146, NULL, 'tanganyika polytechnic college', NULL, '(Ref. No: VET/ARS/PR/2018/C/113)', 27, 216, 'principal@tanpoly.ac.tz', 737008000, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Arusha', 'www.tancollege.ac.tz.', '-', '', 'Tanganyika Polytechnic College (TanCollege) is a vocational training institution Registered by the Vocational Education and Training Authority.\r\nPrograms and courses\r\nCertificate Courses (11 courses)\r\nCertificate in Computer Applications(Computer Applications)\r\nCertificate in Tour Guiding Operations(Tour Guiding Operations)\r\nCertificate in Driving Skills(Driving Skills)\r\nCertificate in Entrepreneurship(Entrepreneurship)\r\nCertificate in Music(Music)\r\nCertificate in Graphic Design, TV Motion Graphics & Video Production,\r\nCertificate in Graphic design and Video Production\r\nCertificate in Tailoring and Fashion Design\r\nCertificate in Electrical and Solar Installation\r\nCertificate in Art and Design in African Culture\r\nCertificate in Computer Maintenance\r\nDiploma Courses (3 courses)\r\nDiploma in Information Communication Technology(ICT)\r\nDiploma in Electrical Installation\r\nDiploma in Designing, Sewing and Clothing Technology.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 13:48:13', '2024-07-28 13:48:13'),
(147, NULL, 'St. Gabriel VTC and motor vehicle Workshop.', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'mt.gabriel@yahoo.com', 754488293, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'P.O.BOX 3044, ARUSHA', 'https://mabumbe.com › st-gabriel', '-', '', 'St. Gabriel Vtc in Tanzania is a VETA Registered Centre with a vision to empower and prepare their students for the labour market and self-employment (chuo cha St. Gabriel Vtc | VETA St. Gabriel Vtc). Their mission is to create a good learning environment which meets the Education, Training and Development expectations of their students.\r\nA student wishing to study at St. Gabriel Vtc should apply online or physically attend to St. Gabriel Vtc to seek for admissions or fetch the application form..', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 13:56:17', '2024-07-28 13:56:17'),
(148, NULL, 'VETA Igogo Mwanza', NULL, '-', 27, 216, 'info@iae.ac.tz', 222150838, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'P. O. Box 22,Mwanza', 'https://www.veta.go.tz', '-', '', 'To ensure availability of Vocational Skills in Tanzania through provision and promotion of Vocational Education and Training (VET) to meet labour market demand for socioeconomic development.”\r\nVETA is charged with the role of promoting vocational education and training in the country. VETA believes that the public can support VET if it is provided with adequate information about VET goals and activities. Promotion is carried by communicating VET to different stakeholders including the government, parents, employers, employees, and donors. Also, current and prospective trainees, instructors, VET graduates legislators, trade unions, NGOs and the media..\r\nVETA uses different media in communicating VET to stakeholders: through advertising, VET week activities, public presentations, trade fairs and exhibitions and publicity. Others include newsletters, annual reports, brochures, VET catalogues, website and other promotional materials.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-28 14:15:21', '2024-07-28 14:15:21'),
