(164, NULL, 'Tanesco regional office Dodoma', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'customer.service@tanesco.co.tz', 748550000, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'P.O.Box 453 Dodoma', 'https://www.tanesco.co.tz', '-', '20240729110506.png', 'Tanzania Electric Supply Company Limited (TANESCO) is a Parastatal organization established by Memorandum and Articles of Association incorporated on 26th November 1931 which established Tanzania Electric Supply Company Limited (the then Tanganyika Electric Supply Company Limited -TANESCO). The Company generates, purchases, transmits, distributes, and sells electricity to Tanzania Mainland and sells bulk power to the Zanzibar Electricity Corporation (ZECO), which in turn sells it to the public in islands Unguja and Pemba. TANESCO owns most of the electricity generating, transmitting, and distributing facilities in Tanzania Mainland with an estimated population of over 50 million.\r\n\r\nHistorically, the German colonialists established the first public electricity supply in Tanzania, the then called Tanganyika in 1908 at Dar es Salaam. It served the railway workshops and a part of the town where the colonialists were mostly staying. In 1920, when Tanganyika territory was put under Great Britain protectorate, a Government Electricity Department was formed to take over and operate the public supplies left by the Germans. In 1931, the Government handed over the undertaking at Dar es Salaam and those elsewhere upcountry (Dodoma, Tabora, and Kigoma) to private enterprises. One of these companies was the Tanganyika Electric Supply Company Ltd. (TANESCO) and the other Company was the Dar es Salaam and District Electric Supply Company Ltd (DARESCO). The two companies were merged in 1964 and later changed their name into Tanzania Electric Supply Company (TANESCO).', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 16:05:06', '2024-07-29 16:05:06'),
(165, NULL, 'Mobisol Dodoma', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'INFO@TANZANIAMAILING.CO.TZ', 766550600, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Dodoma', 'www.tanzaniamailing.com', '-', '', 'Mobisol is a leading German company for prepaid Solar Home Systems (SHS) dedicated to delivering a clean, affordable alternative to fossil fuels for low-income households living without access to reliable energy. Mobisol’s products combine solar energy with innovative mobile technology and microfinance. Mobisol is currently serving over 30,000 customers in Tanzania and Rwanda. Mobisol is aspiring to scale rapidly in order to reach hundreds of thousands of households in off grid communities – thereby stimulating economic and social development in project countries while simultaneously contributing to global environmental protection.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 16:15:17', '2024-07-29 16:15:17'),
(166, NULL, 'Ewura head office', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@ewura.go.tz', 262329002, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'First Floor, · 3 EWURA Street, · 41104 Tambukareli,  P.O Box 2857, · Dodoma, Tanzania', 'www.ewura.go.tz', '-', '20240729112205.jpg', 'The Energy and Water Utilities Regulatory Authority (EWURA) is an autonomous multi-sectoral regulatory authority established by the EWURA Act Cap 414 of the laws of Tanzania. It is responsible for technical and economic regulation of the electricity, petroleum, natural gas and water sectors in Tanzania pursuant to Cap 414 and sector legislation.\r\nThe functions of EWURA include among others, to issue licenses, regulating rates and charges, making rules, monitoring the performance of the regulated sectors, facilitating resolution of complaints and disputes between service providers and consumers of regulated goods and services and disseminate information about matters relevant to its functions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 16:22:05', '2024-07-29 16:22:05'),
(167, NULL, 'L & T  constructions Tanzania', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'infodesk@larsentoubro.com', 222129050, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Junction of Lugalo and Magore Street at Upanga, Amverton Office Park, First Floor, Magore St, Dar es Salaam', 'https://www.larsentoubro.com', '-', '20240729113151.jpg', 'Headquartered in Mumbai, Larsen & Toubro Limited is one of the largest and most respected companies in India\'s private sector. With over 80 years of a strong, customer focused approach and a continuous quest for world-class quality, L&T has unmatched capabilities across Technology, Engineering, Construction, and Manufacturing, and maintains a leadership in all its major lines of business.\r\nA thrust on international business over the years has seen L&T\'s global footprint growing steadily. We have manufacturing facilities in key geographies, and offices and customers in over 30 countries.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 16:31:51', '2024-07-29 16:31:51'),
(168, NULL, 'Sagar energy solutions', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@sagarenergysolutions.re', 768334334, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Kirumba, Mwanza', 'www.sagarenergysolutions.re/', '-', '', 'Sagar Energy Solutions is an ambitious clean-tech start-up that targets productive loads in the industrial sector of East Africa. Our mission is ‘to transition niche and artisanal businesses away from fossil fuel dependence and towards renewable energy solutions.’\r\nCurrently, in Lake Victoria, over 160,000,000 USD are spent every year on over 216,000,000 litres of kerosene to fuel pressurised kerosene lanterns to attract a type of sardine at night. This sardine equals over 50% of the lake’s yearly catch, is the main source of protein for the entire region and provides jobs for millions of people. This night fishing industry is an incredibly productive sector, yet is fully reliant on an unsustainable practice, posing economic burdens to the fishermen and their families, significant negative health effects, and it also emits over 400,000 tonnes of CO2 a year.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 16:42:04', '2024-07-29 16:42:04'),
(169, NULL, 'Mwanza urban water and sanitation authority', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@mwauwasa.go.tz', 282500547, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Maji House Barabara ya Balewa S.L.P 317, MWANZA', 'https://www.mwauwasa.go.tz', '-', '', 'Mwanza Urban Water Supply and Sanitation Authority (MWAUWASA) was established in July 1996 under Water Works Ordinance Cap 281 (as amended by Act no 8 1997 of) as a semi autonomous executive agency of the government for provision of adequate, reliable and sustainable portable water and waste water management services in Mwanza City at affordable and cost effective prices. It was declared full autonomous from January 1998 and was authorized to extend services to Kisesa Township in Magu District from September 2007. The Authority is wholly owned by the Government of Tanzania.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 16:47:10', '2024-07-29 16:47:10'),
(170, NULL, 'Power providers company limited', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@powerproviders.co.tz', 739502300, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'P.O. Box 16462, Arusha, Tanzania', 'www.powerproviders.co.tz', '-', '', 'An axiom of business is that it should be economically viable, generating from its sales more than those sales cost, plus overheads. That is a necessary principle for starting a business but not a sufficient one: many entrepreneurs never look beyond that principle and indeed their measure of success is how big that surplus can be and how rich they can get. But it is surely better to judge an enterprise on its contribution to the wellbeing of society and not just on how big it is.\r\n\r\nIn the case of Power Providers the cart definitely follows the horse. The green energy business that Clive Jones set up five years ago in the northern Tanzanian town of Arusha is a commercial success by any standards, having grown from zero to an annual turnover of more than $1 million. But it has been grown on its founder’s conviction that developing alternatives to fossil fuels is imperative for human survival—something every schoolchild knows, but is impeded by political and commercial inertia.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:10:26', '2024-07-29 19:10:26'),
(171, NULL, 'Energy devices company limited', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@powerproviders.co.tz', 767959010, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Nairobi Rd, Arusha 14207', 'www.edc-power.co.tz', '-', '', 'Energy Devices Company Ltd in cooperation with Bredenoord brings you Generator rentals, now in the northern zone of Tanzania.\r\nEnergy Devices has developed key partners throughout India that have supported the growth of our brands. We understand the need to offer choices to our customers and offer a range of technologies, price points and services. We align ourselves to brands that have the same values as ours namely service and support, quality and value for money. All our products are backed by warranties held in India and our experience as well as knowledge sets us apart from our competitors. Our commitment to serving the customer’ needs is paramount.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:18:36', '2024-07-29 19:18:36'),
(172, NULL, 'Tecnix tz', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'pmbjerre@yahoo.dk', 659651505, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'P.O. Box 2398 Olasiti – Arusha, Tanzania.', 'https://tecnixtz.wordpress.com', '-', '', 'Tecnix Tanzania was established in 2010 to provide homes and businesses with green, renewable energy produced with materials local to Tanzania. Our years of experience with building, installing and maintaining wind generators in Tanzania have allowed us to learn, and thereby improve and refine our wind generators to suit the Tanzanian context.\r\nWind is a renewable resource – one of the most efficient and environmentally friendly sources of power to use[1].  Wind generators do not take up much space, and they harness wind power with very little pollution. While solar panels can be useful, they only produce power when the sun is shining (9 hours max on a good day), and require large, expensive batteries to store power for 24/7 use.  Solar panels are also less efficient at producing energy compared to wind generators and give off more CO2 per kWh.1\r\nWind generators are of course dependent on wind, and sometimes the wind speed is too slow to produce power. However, our system is designed to harvest good power in low wind speeds which is most common but they are also built to survive the high wind speeds and storms.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:23:35', '2024-07-29 19:23:35'),
(173, NULL, 'Protons energy ltd', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@photonenergy.com', 762067467, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Sakina opposite Suma Jkt Along Arusha-Namanga', 'https://photonsenergy.com', '-', '', 'Photons Energy Ltd is a local EPC company providing end-to-end solar energy services.\r\n\r\nWe design, procure, install, maintain & operate tailor-made solar solutions for both residential & commercial clients across Tanzania.\r\nWe are also a Renewable Energy Components Distribution Company, providing genuine products from reputable manufacturers across the globe.\r\nPhotons Energy Limited is fast growing renewable energy company. We deal with Design, Supply and Installation of Renewable Energy Systems.\r\nAll the projects including the Design, Consultation, Supply and Installation of Renewable Energy Systems', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:31:38', '2024-07-29 19:31:38'),
(174, NULL, 'State oil', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@stategroup.co.tz', 685535558, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Shekilango Rd, Dar es Salaam', 'https://www.stategroup.co.tz', '-', '', 'StateOil Tanzania was founded on the premise that there is a great future for Tanzania and Africa.\r\nStateOil Tanzania was formed and is run by professionals with vivid experience and wide exposure in the oil industry. We have proved commitment to high levels of efficiency, reliability, clean deliveries, timely reporting, and loss-free services.\r\nIn all our processes, safety is one of our foremost priorities. We aspire to be the most reputable, successful and progressive bulk fuel trader and transporters in East and Central Africa.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:38:54', '2024-07-29 19:38:54'),
(175, NULL, 'Tanzania petroleum development company', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@tpdc.co.tz', 222200103, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Jakaya Kikwete Road , PSSF Kambarage Tower, 8th Floor, P.O.Box 1191, DODOMA', 'https://tpdc.co.tz', '-', '', 'It gives me great pleasure to welcome you, on behalf of the Management and TPDC Staff to our Website.\r\n\r\nTPDC is undergoing massive reforms aimed at increasing our presence in the hydrocarbon value chain. TPDC intends to do this through its subsidiaries (GASCO and TANOIL).\r\nWe have a vision to become a globally competitive company and a key player in the Oil and Gas industry both regionally and internationally. At TPDC team success precedes individual success, an ideal we hold dear to our hearts. We trust each other to deliver on our obligations and constantly strive to achieve quality outcomes.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:44:32', '2024-07-29 19:44:32'),
(176, NULL, 'Equinor Tanzania', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'gm_dataprotection@equinor.com', 222664707, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Block A, 429 Mahando St, Dar es Salaam', 'https://www.equinor.com', '-', '', 'Equinor has been in Tanzania since 2007 when the company signed a Production Sharing Agreement (PSA) for Block 2 with Tanzania Petroleum Development Corporation (TPDC).\r\n\r\nEquinor Tanzania is the Operator with 65% participating interest while ExxonMobil is partner with a 35% working interest. TPDC has the right to participate with a 10% interest.\r\n\r\nMajor gas discoveries have been made offshore Tanzania and the country is emerging as a potential large gas producer in East Africa.\r\nEquinor started exploration drilling activities in Block 2 Offshore Tanzania in 2011. A total of 15 exploration wells have been drilled, resulting in nine discoveries with estimated volumes of more than 20 Tcf of gas in place.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:49:39', '2024-07-29 19:49:39'),
(177, NULL, 'Asam oil company limited', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@asamoil.co.tz', 713570608, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'odacom Tower, Morocco, 2nd Floor, Bagamoyo Road Dar es salaam TZ, 15730', 'https://asamoil.co.tz', '-', '', 'Asamoil Company Limited is a commercially wholly owned by the young and energic entrepreneur Azhad Soud Abdulrahim. Asamoil company limited  started wholesale of petroleum products in June 2014 and it is located at Dar es salaam, fire sikukuu street.\r\n\r\nWe are one of the best leading energy suppliers and primary catalyst for economy growth in Tanzania. We have played an integral role in Tanzania economic development.\r\n\r\nThe company has the following core objectives.\r\nDevelop and invest in profitable business within Tanzania\r\nCreate a meaningful employment within Tanzania\r\nGrow talent – business leaders and professionals.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:53:30', '2024-07-29 19:53:30'),
(178, NULL, 'Oilcom limited terminal', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'oilcom@oilcomtz.com', 222125312, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Dar Es Salaam. P O Box 20831', 'https://www.oilcomtz.com', '-', '', '22 glorious years in the domain of importing, distributing and marketing Petroleum Products across East and Central Africa-such are the credentials of OILCOM Tanzania Limited. The company came into existence on 26th July 1990 and since then, began a new chapter of success, service and excellence in the trade of Oil & Petroleum Products. Headquartered in Dar es Salaam, the main port and commercial capital of Tanzania, the company has taken huge strides towards expansion in neighboring countries of Malawi, Rwanda, Burundi, Zambia, Kenya, and the Democratic Republic of Congo', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 19:57:03', '2024-07-29 19:57:03'),
(179, NULL, 'Lake oil ltd', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'admin@lakeoilgroup.com', 678206838, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Dar es Salaam Kigamboni Dar es Salaam TZ, 5055.', 'https://www.lakeoilgroup.com', '-', '', 'Lake Group is one of East and Central Africa\'s fastest growing energy trading and transportation conglomerates. Ally Edha Awadh the young and energetic entrepreneur founded the first company in Group \'Lake Oil\' in year 2006 at age of 27. Over the years Lake Oil has established a strong footprint in all East and Central African countries and is now one of the 5 largest distributors of petroleum products in Tanzania. Being the mother company, Lake Oil is the strongest entity of the Group with other verticals such as Lake Trans, Lake Gas, Gulf Cement and Concrete Products and most recent addition being African Inland Container Depot. Lake Group is geographically spread across every region of Tanzania and also neighboring countries of Zambia, DRC, Burundi, Rwanda and Kenya. The secret behind our success is by providing highest service standards, providing quality and consistent supply of fuel and customer care.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 20:01:23', '2024-07-29 20:01:23'),
(180, NULL, 'Dalbit petroleum ltd', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'info@dalbitinternational.com', 222863247, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '2nd Floor, www.dalbitpetroleum.com, Azania Plaza, 9122 Julius K. Nyerere Rd, Dar es Salaam', 'https://www.dalbitpetroleum.com › ...', '-', '', 'Dalbit is a member of the Janus Continental Group (JCG) with presence and operations in nine countries in the Eastern, Central, and Southern African regions. \r\n\r\nIt is a progressive and customer-centric petroleum supply company offering total energy solutions with expertise in the distribution, storage and bulk-trading of petroleum products and related services.\r\nOur founder established the first petroleum company, Congo Petrol, in 1997. Dalbit Petroleum in Kenya followed shortly thereafter in 2002. \r\n\r\nSince then, Dalbit has been striving to become a leading provider of total energy solutions in Eastern, Central, and Southern Africa through its reliable distribution networks.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-07-29 20:06:03', '2024-07-29 20:06:03'),
(181, NULL, 'Lake oil ltd', NULL, '-', 28, 216, 'admin@lakeoilgroup.com', 678206838, NULL, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, 'Dar es Salaam Kigamboni Dar es Salaam', 'https://www.lakeoilgroup.com', NULL, '', 'Lake Group was established by its founding CEO and Chairman Mr. Ally Edha Awadh in 2006 with the opening of its flagship Company \'Lake Oil\' with a very humble beginning. Since inception the growth story of Lake Group was vertical and has become one of the fastest growing energy trading, logistics and construction supply material Conglomerate in East and Central Africa and Middle East.\r\nOver the years, Lake Group has successfully ventured into various business activities covering Downstream Oil & Gas sector, Logistics Solutions, Manufacturing & construction Industries Like Steel, Lubricants and Premix Concrete, Port extension services like Inland Container Depots.\r\nLake Group distributes and trades white Petroleum products in Tanzania, Zambia, DRC, Burundi, Kenya,Ethiopia and Rwanda; owns its own oil storage facilities in Tanzania, Kenya, Burundi and the Democratic Republic of Congo; manufactures lubes and Ready Mix Concrete, and operates a fleet of more than 700 trucks. As an MNC, with its headquarters in Dar Es’ Salaam, Tanzania, Lake Group provides quality products and Services of daily consumption in a safe, efficient and cost-effective manner without damaging the environment.\r\nWith its uncompromising standards of excellence, Lake Group is geographically spread across all over East and Central Africa with one of its largest Premix Plant is located in Dubai.\r\nThe Group is having diverse mix of 21 nationalities with a total work force of 4600 Plus employees of various caliber.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, '0', NULL, '2024-08-05 18:23:49', '2024-08-05 18:23:49'),
